Sentencas: The wet powder spraying (WPS) technique was used for the deposition of dense and thin (Y2O3)(0.08)(ZrO2)(0.92) (YSZ-8) films on an anode substrate being used for fuel cell applications.
Titulo: Fabrication of an anode-supported yttria-stabilized zirconia thin film for solid-oxide fuel cells via wet powder spraying

Sentencas: Both agglomeration of the powder and the presence of organics in the substrate have a significant effect on the quality and densification of the thin electrolyte layer.
Titulo: Fabrication of an anode-supported yttria-stabilized zirconia thin film for solid-oxide fuel cells via wet powder spraying

Sentencas: High-energy ball milling effectively broke up the agglomerates and enhanced the packing density of the green layer.
Titulo: Fabrication of an anode-supported yttria-stabilized zirconia thin film for solid-oxide fuel cells via wet powder spraying

Sentencas: Pre-calcination of the substrate at similar to 1000 degrees C enhanced the match of sintering shrinkage between the electrolyte layer and the substrate and improved the quality of the YSZ-8 thin film significantly.
Titulo: Fabrication of an anode-supported yttria-stabilized zirconia thin film for solid-oxide fuel cells via wet powder spraying

Sentencas: Crack-free dual-layer assembly with a highly densified YSZ-8 film as thin as 10 mu m was successfully fabricated by optimizing the fabrication parameters.
Titulo: Fabrication of an anode-supported yttria-stabilized zirconia thin film for solid-oxide fuel cells via wet powder spraying

Sentencas: The cells with a La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 cathode showed a high open circuit voltage of 1.071 V and a peak power density of 894 mW cm(-2) at 850 degrees C operated with hydrogen fuel.
Titulo: Fabrication of an anode-supported yttria-stabilized zirconia thin film for solid-oxide fuel cells via wet powder spraying
